# The [[property]] of [[sticking#Noun|sticking]] or [[adhering#Noun|adhering]]; [[adhesion]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Olivia Judson|authorlink=Olivia Judson|title=The hemiparasite season [print version: Under the hemiparasite, ''International New York Times'', 24–25 December 2014, page&nbsp;7]|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/24/opinion/the-hemiparasite-season.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141223181330/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/24/opinion/the-hemiparasite-season.html|archivedate=23 December 2014|newspaper={{w|The New York Times}}|date=23 December 2014|passage={{...}} The flesh [of the [[mistletoe]] berry] is sticky, and forms strings and ribbons between my thumb and forefinger. For the mistletoe, this viscous goop&nbsp;– and by the way, viscous comes to English from [[Viscum|viscum]]&nbsp;– is crucial. The '''stickiness''' means that, after eating the berries, birds often regurgitate the seeds and then wipe their bills on twigs&nbsp;– leading to the seeds' getting glued to the tree, where they can germinate and begin the cycle anew.}}
# [[warmth|Warmth]] and [[humidity]], as on a [[muggy]] day.
# {{lb|en|economics}}: Of [[price#Noun|prices]] or [[wage]]s: the [[tendency]] to stay the same despite [[change#Noun|changes]] in the [[economy]].
# {{lb|en|marketing|interface design}} The [[presence]] of [[unique]] [[attribute#Noun|attributes]] that make a [[product]] [[indisposable]] and [[valuable]] to its [[owner]].
#: {{ux|en|The '''stickiness''' of a cellphone might be measured by its ability to tell correct time, locate its user, and allow its user to remain connected regardless of location.}}
# {{lb|en|advertising}} A [[research#Noun|research]] [[measure#Noun|measure]] that [[capture#Verb|captures]] the extent to which [[viewer]]s wish to spend more time looking at or reading a [[print#Adjective|print]] [[advertisement]].
#: {{ux|en|The low '''stickiness''' rating helped explain why our ad’s [[brand linkage]] rating was so low: people were turned off by the blurriness of the main photo.}}
# {{lb|en|psychology}} An [[overemotional]] [[attachment]] to others; [[clinging#Noun|clinging]] in [[interpersonal]] [[relation]]s; [[difficulty]] with [[end#Verb|ending]] [[conversation]]s.

